cs.SY, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.DC 

The paper deals with control systems that communicate over unreliable networks, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses communication networks and packet loss, which are relevant to the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category. The use of dead-beat control laws and linear-quadratic loss also suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) sub-categories. Finally, the study of event-triggered control systems could also place the paper in the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category.
